						<div class="bbWrapper" bis_skin_checked="1"><h2><b><a href="https://github.com/isucksunstoes69-dotcom/SmpUtils-bugs-suggestions/issues" target="_blank" class="link link--external" rel="nofollow ugc noopener">https://github.com/isucksunstoes69-dotcom/SmpUtils-bugs-suggestions/issues</a> (suggestions and bug repos here)</b>​</h2><h2>​</h2><h2>​</h2><h2>​</h2><h2>Key Features:​</h2><b>Main Settings GUI</b> - Toggles and adjusts:<br>
<br>
<ul>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Item bans (Netherite, Mace, Pearls, Crystals)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">PvP restrictions (ban PvP, crystal explosions, naked killing)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Potion restrictions (ban specific potions or all potions, tier 2 upgrades)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Dimension access (allow/disable Nether &amp; End)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Cooldown timers (mace, ender pearl, e-gap, wind charge, shield)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Enchantment level caps (Sharpness, Protection)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Special features (health indicator, villager protection)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Pearl Cooldown (to delay pearls)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Wind charge (cooldown to delay wind charges)</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">egap cooldown and much more</li>
</ul><b>Item Limiting System</b> - Prevents players from holding too many of specific items; excess items are automatically dropped<br>
<br>
<b>Ritual System</b> - Creates an animated ritual effect with:<br>
<br>
<ul>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Customizable particle circles</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Boss bar showing ritual progress with coordinates</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Dynamic color changes</li>
<li data-xf-list-type="ul">Configurable duration and radius</li>
</ul><b>Potion Management</b> - Individual toggles for all 14 potion effects plus tier 2 potion restriction<br>
<br>
<b>Enchantment Control</b> - Caps maximum enchantment levels on player gear<br>
<br>
<b>Damage Prevention</b> - Blocks unwanted PvP scenarios (shield cooldowns, axe disarming, naked protection)<br>
<br>
Perfect for heavily customized survival servers that need fine-grained control over gameplay features!<br>
<br>
usage<br>
<br>
/itemlimit &lt;number&gt;<br>
/ritual<br>
/setting</div>
					

					
